text: By delivering vaccines that are effective, safe, and free, our administration has worked to ensure Americans can be together again with their loved ones this Thanksgiving.
name: Kamala Harris
description: Fighting for the people. Wife, Momala, Auntie. She/her. Official account is @VP.

text:
Today, we have effectively closed the gap in vaccination rates for Black and Brown adults. 

We must continue to focus on equity to build a path out of this pandemic.
name: Kamala Harris
description: Fighting for the people. Wife, Momala, Auntie. She/her. Official account is @VP.

text:
Nearly 2M women have been locked out of the workforce during the pandemic, often due to lack of accessible, affordable child and elder care.

Our Build Back Better Framework will establish universal pre-K and lower costs for caregiving to help families get back on their feet.
name: Kamala Harris
description: Fighting for the people. Wife, Momala, Auntie. She/her. Official account is @VP.

text: The COVID-19 vaccines are safe and effective—and the best way to protect our kids. Children between the ages of 5-11 are now eligible to get vaccinated.
name: Kamala Harris
description: Fighting for the people. Wife, Momala, Auntie. She/her. Official account is @VP.

text:
More than 193 million Americans are now fully vaccinated, children 5 and up are eligible to receive the vaccine, and the economy added more than half a million jobs in October. 

We are accelerating the path out of this pandemic.
name: Kamala Harris
description: Fighting for the people. Wife, Momala, Auntie. She/her. Official account is @VP.

text: The pandemic is not yet behind us. But with this week’s announcement of vaccines for kids, 70% of American adults being vaccinated, and a growing economy, our plan to accelerate a path out of the pandemic is working.

description: Fighting for the people. Wife, Momala, Auntie. She/her. Official account is @VP.

text: The Biden-Harris administration has secured enough vaccine supply for every child in America. Parents of children between the ages of 5-11 will be able to bring their child to one of tens of thousands of vaccine locations across the country.
